String concetanation:

works with "+" operator 
string = string + "string2"

Type Coercion:

Java script engine coerces the value to the appropriate data type. This happens with the "==" operator.
If no coercing is desired then one has to use "===" operator


False values :
null
""
undefined
0
false

True values:
true,
"hello"
1
-1

Braces :
Should always start on the same line 
correct :
if(){
	
}

incorrect :
if()
{
	
}

Elements of style:
semicolon should be specified to terminate each statement;
